    <div class="content-pane">
      <div class="content-pane-body">
        <h1 id="overview">libMPGO — MPEG-O Objective-C Reference Implementation</h1>
        <p>
          libMPGO is the reference implementation of the MPEG-O multi-omics data
          standard. It provides Objective-C classes and protocols for authoring,
          reading, querying, encrypting, and signing <code>.mpgo</code> files
          (HDF5 container format).
        </p>
        <p>
          All classes listed in the left navigation are public API. Cross-language
          equivalents in Python (<code>mpeg_o.*</code>) and Java
          (<code>com.dtwthalion.mpgo.*</code>) are documented in the class
          comments where they exist.
        </p>

        <h2 id="classes">Core classes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOSpectralDataset.html#class$MPGOSpectralDataset">MPGOSpectralDataset</a> — top-level container for acquisition runs</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOAcquisitionRun.html#class$MPGOAcquisitionRun">MPGOAcquisitionRun</a> — single LC-MS / NMR run with spectra, chromatograms, identifications</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOMassSpectrum.html#class$MPGOMassSpectrum">MPGOMassSpectrum</a> — mass-spectrum axis (m/z, intensity)</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGONMRSpectrum.html#class$MPGONMRSpectrum">MPGONMRSpectrum</a> — 1D NMR spectrum</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOMSImage.html#class$MPGOMSImage">MPGOMSImage</a> — MS-imaging (MALDI) dataset</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Storage providers</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOHDF5Provider.html#class$MPGOHDF5Provider">MPGOHDF5Provider</a> — canonical HDF5 back-end</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOSqliteProvider.html#class$MPGOSqliteProvider">MPGOSqliteProvider</a> — single-file SQLite back-end (Provisional)</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOMemoryProvider.html#class$MPGOMemoryProvider">MPGOMemoryProvider</a> — in-memory provider for tests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Protection</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOEncryptionManager.html#class$MPGOEncryptionManager">MPGOEncryptionManager</a> — AES-256-GCM intensity-channel encryption</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOSignatureManager.html#class$MPGOSignatureManager">MPGOSignatureManager</a> — HMAC-SHA256 v2 canonical signatures</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOAccessPolicy.html#class$MPGOAccessPolicy">MPGOAccessPolicy</a> — access-control policy JSON</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOAnonymizer.html#class$MPGOAnonymizer">MPGOAnonymizer</a> — one-shot anonymization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Import / export</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOMzMLReader.html#class$MPGOMzMLReader">MPGOMzMLReader</a> / <a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOMzMLWriter.html#class$MPGOMzMLWriter">MPGOMzMLWriter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGONmrMLReader.html#class$MPGONmrMLReader">MPGONmrMLReader</a> / <a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGONmrMLWriter.html#class$MPGONmrMLWriter">MPGONmrMLWriter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOISAExporter.html#class$MPGOISAExporter">MPGOISAExporter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOThermoRawReader.html#class$MPGOThermoRawReader">MPGOThermoRawReader</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="protocols">Domain protocols</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOCVAnnotatable.html#protocol$(MPGOCVAnnotatable)">MPGOCVAnnotatable</a> — controlled-vocabulary annotation</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOEncryptable.html#protocol$(MPGOEncryptable)">MPGOEncryptable</a> — intensity-channel encryption</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOIndexable.html#protocol$(MPGOIndexable)">MPGOIndexable</a> — spectrum-index construction</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOProvenanceable.html#protocol$(MPGOProvenanceable)">MPGOProvenanceable</a> — provenance metadata</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="MPGOStreamable.html#protocol$(MPGOStreamable)">MPGOStreamable</a> — streaming read/write</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <em>Every class page carries the full class sidebar on the left. Start
          anywhere.</em>
        </p>
